        <hl1>THE MARKETS: COMMODITIES</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Gold for August delivery rises 3.2 percent to $284.20 per ounce; graph of commodities prices (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>GOLD SURGES. Gold rose on expectations that a weaker dollar will increase investor demand for the precious metal. Gold for August delivery rose $8.80, or 3.2 percent, to $284.20 an ounce in New York.</p>
      </block>
